    "detail": "Nice hotel with good size rooms which is rare in Paris at that rate. The breakfast spread is good with western and some Japanese. As the hotel is just opposite to the Gare Du Nord, it makes commuting to other city like Bordeaux much more convenient. The hote is also central to two Metro station and makes sight-seeing and touring Paris a breeze. Also there are lots ofgood cafe restaurant nearby. Only complain is that the check in time is aroudn 3pm so travellers arriving in the morning might have to wait some time before they are allocated their rooms. The nice lobby makes a good resting place while waiting with free wifi assses. ",
